The Bayelsa State House of Assembly has elected, Rt. Hon. Abraham Ingobere, the member representing Brass Constituency 3 and Hon. Micheal Ogbere, representing Ekeremor Constituency 3 as Speaker and Deputy Speaker respectively. Rt. Hon. Ingobere, a third-term legislator of the Peoples Democratic Party, took over from Rt. Hon. Monday Obolo, the member representing Southern Ijaw constituency 2. ALSO READ: BREAKING: Bayelsa speaker steps down BREAKING: Bayelsa speaker steps down PDP to CJN: Reconstitute panel on Imo election Bayelsa: PDP Reps caucus calls for prosecution of… UPDATE: Buhari no longer listening to anyone ― PDP Other elected principal officers are, Rt. Hon. Obolo, Majority Leader and Micheal Ogbere representing Ekeremor Constituency 3, Chief Whip. In his remarks, the new elected Speaker said he is grateful for the house for electing him as the speaker and promised to run an all-inclusive government. “I promise to work together with all the members of the Assembly irrespective of their political party, while working closely with the executive arm of the state government. “I will ensure that the will of Bayelsa people are done, by implementing good policies, for the interest of the general public.” SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.